The paper discusses a hardware accelerator for convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on precision and tailoring it to the values of activations suggests a potential fit for the sub-category of numerical analysis (cs.NA). The use of on-the-fly detection and adjustment of precision also suggests a potential fit for the sub-category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a practical implementation of the hardware accelerator, which could potentially fit under the sub-category of architecture (cs.AR).
